.TH HSH 1 "August 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [ script ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX shell implemented in C as part of the Holberton School curriculum.
It provides a command-line interface where users can type commands, execute them,
and interact with the operating system.

The shell supports both interactive and non-interactive modes:
.IP \(bu
In interactive mode, it displays a prompt (\fB#cisfun$\fR) and waits for user input.
.IP \(bu
In non-interactive mode, it executes commands received from a script or piped input.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Command execution
Supports execution of programs using either their absolute/relative path or by searching in the \fBPATH\fR environment variable.
.TP
.B Built-in commands
.IP \(bu
\fBexit\fR \- exits the shell
.IP \(bu
\fBenv\fR \- prints the current environment
.TP
.B Error handling
If a command cannot be found or executed, an error message is displayed and the prompt reappears.
.TP
.B Arguments
Supports command lines with arguments.
.TP
.B End of file
Properly handles end-of-file condition (\fBCtrl+D\fR).

.SH OPTIONS
Currently, \fBhsh\fR does not support command-line options.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive usage:
.EX
$ ./hsh
#cisfun$ ls -l
#cisfun$ echo "Hello World"
#cisfun$ exit
.EE

Non-interactive usage:
.EX
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
$ ./hsh < script.sh
.EE

.SH LIMITATIONS
This shell does not yet support advanced features such as:
.IP \(bu
Directory navigation (\fBcd\fR)
.IP \(bu
Pipelines (\fB|\fR)
.IP \(bu
I/O redirection (\fB>\fR, \fB<\fR)

.SH AUTHOR
Lapique Philippe <ph.lapique@example.com>

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR zsh (1)
